# CODEOWNERS — canonical shape per docs/REPO_STANDARDS.md §7.
#
# Single-owner phase: all patterns route to @${CODEOWNER_HANDLE}. v2 fans out per-
# domain reviewers (docs → docs-savvy, workflows → security-savvy) as
# the team grows. Do NOT prematurely fan out — keep single-owner until
# there is more than one reviewer to route to.
#
# Adoption per tier (see REPO_STANDARDS.md §2 branch-protection table):
#   - governance + umbrella tiers: CODEOWNERS review is REQUIRED
#     (branch protection `require_code_owner_reviews: true`).
#   - product-code + ops-private tiers: CODEOWNERS ships but does NOT
#     gate merges (defer to `ai-review.yml` + `composition.yml`).
#
# CRITICAL ordering invariant: GitHub CODEOWNERS is LAST-MATCH-WINS.
# Broad globs go FIRST; specific paths go LAST — otherwise a later
# broad rule silently overrides an earlier specific one. Preserve
# this ordering when fanning out to per-domain reviewers in v2, or
# governance paths (CLAUDE.md, DECISIONS.md, REPO_STANDARDS.md) will
# quietly re-route to the docs owner.

# Global default: founder
*                                       @${CODEOWNER_HANDLE}

# Docs (broad glob — must come BEFORE governance-surface files that
# live under docs/, so the specific rules below win)
docs/**                                 @${CODEOWNER_HANDLE}

# Security-sensitive paths
.github/**                              @${CODEOWNER_HANDLE}
.github/workflows/**                    @${CODEOWNER_HANDLE}
.github/ai-review/**                    @${CODEOWNER_HANDLE}

# Governance surfaces (specific files — LAST so they win over
# the broader docs/** and .github/** rules above)
CLAUDE.md                               @${CODEOWNER_HANDLE}
ops/DECISIONS.md                        @${CODEOWNER_HANDLE}
docs/REPO_STANDARDS.md                  @${CODEOWNER_HANDLE}
